The paper deals with improving lower bounds on the rate-memory tradeoffs for coded caching, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The caching scenario also involves networked information (cs.NI) and communication complexity (cs.CC). The use of coding techniques and optimization methods may also fall under signal processing (cs.SI).
